<html>
  <head>
    <title>Nine-Tailed Fox - Creature Codex</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600&family=Cinzel+Decorative:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/style.css" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a href="/#big-logo" class="header-CreatureCodex">Creature Codex</a>
      <nav class="header-nav">
        <a href="/#about" class="header-link">About</a>
        <a href="/#new-creatures" class="header-link header-link-creatures">I got New Creatures!</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="header-search">
        <input type="text" placeholder="Search" />
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="creature-page">
      <div class="creature-hero">
        <div class="creature-info">
          <h1>Nine-Tailed Fox (九尾狐)</h1>
          <div class="creature-meta">
            <p>Type: Spirit Beast</p>
            <p>Origin: Ancient Chinese Mythology</p>
            <p>The Nine-Tailed Fox is a mysterious fox spirit known for its intelligence and magical power. It is said to live deep in the mountains and forests, and its many tails represent its age and supernatural abilities. In some legends, the creature can transform into a human and interact with people. Depending on the story, the Nine-Tailed Fox may appear as either a wise spirit or a dangerous trickster.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="creature-illustration">
          <img src="/creature%20pictures/NineTailsFox.jpg" alt="Nine-Tailed Fox illustration">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="creature-related">
        <h2>Relevant Creatures</h2>
        <div class="relevant-grid">
          <div class="relevant-card"></div>
          <div class="relevant-card"></div>
          <div class="relevant-card"></div>
          <div class="relevant-card"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="about-bar">
      <div class="about-logo">
        <img src="/logo.png" alt="Logo">
      </div>
      <div class="about-columns">
        <div class="about-col">
          <h3>About</h3>
          <p>Creature Codex is a community-driven space for people who enjoy imagining and discovering strange creatures. The goal of the website is to bring together creatures from different sources, including ancient mythology, books, games, and personal creations, into one shared archive. More than just a collection, Creature Codex aims to build a creative community where users can explore creatures. By allowing people to add and share new creatures, the website encourages imagination, collaboration, and world-building, turning the codex into a growing universe created by its community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="about-col">
          <h3>Contact</h3>
          <p>Email: creature.codex@gmail.com</p>
          <p>Instagram: @CreatureCodex</p>
          <p>Phone Number: +1 56-1344-0264</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>
</html>